freedesktop-sdk-21.08beta.1:

  * Support for a new architecture: RISC-V
  * Update all the components to the latest version available, check specific versions at
    https://gitlab.com/freedesktop-sdk/freedesktop-sdk/-/wikis/Release-Contents#contents
  * Improve reproducibility tests and fix several components to be reproducible; reproducible
    tests are run in a daily schedule
  * Add schedule job to check license of each element and generate report
  * Remove Rust extension (#1020)
  * Reintroduce gstreamer-vaapi as extension
  * openssl is not part of the bootstrap anymore
  * A lot of other small fixes and improvements

freedesktop-sdk-20.08.0:

   * Disable publish of ARM v7 runtimes

freedesktop-sdk-20.08rc.2:

   * pipewire: Update to 0.3.10 (ABI break: new symbol)
   * Add mini debuginfo in binaries (#767)
   * Fix some repoducibility issue with some debuginfo files
   * docbook-xsl: Switch to version without namespaces. Fixes some man pages
   * libportal: Fix issue with C++ applications (#1099)
   * alsa-lib: Add dmix pcm plugin (#1082) (ABI breaks: new symbols)
   * systemd-libs: Add missing debuginfo.

